Reverce ORM. We do not create tables, we create CRUD queryes and you can add your queryes too.


1) CREATE TABLE (see test/test.sql)

2) CREATE DESC OF TABLE (see test/reverse_orm.json)

3) MAKE SQL QUERYES (start test/make.sh)

4) TEST IT (start test/test.sh)


Example:

$public__test = new public__test__t;

$rc = $public__test->get([ 'filter'=> [ 'id'=> $id, 'flag_valid'=> 'true' ], 'expect_count'=> 1 ]); // get ONE valid row (by PRIMARY KEY)

$rc = $public__test->cnt([ 'filter'=> [ 'flag_valid'=> 'true' ] ]); // get count of all valid rows

$rc = $public__test->get([ 'filter'=> [ 'flag_valid'=> 'true' ], 'sort'=> [ 'id'=> 'DESC' ], 'offset'=> $offset, 'limit'=> $limit ]); // get all valid rows with order by id

$rc = $public__test->del([ 'filter'=> [ 'id'=> $id ] ]); // del row (by PRIMARY KEY)

$rc = $public__test->del(); // del all rows
